  "text": "The Kubernetes scheduler plugin framework is implemented across several key files in the kubernetes/kubernetes repository:\n\n## Framework Interface Definitions\n**pkg/scheduler/framework/interface.go** (lines 443-783) contains the core plugin interface definitions:\n- **Plugin** (line 443): Base interface all plugins must implement\n- **PreEnqueuePlugin** (line 452): Controls which pods enter the scheduling queue\n- **QueueSortPlugin** (line 464): Determines the order of pods in the queue\n- **PreFilterPlugin** (line 512): Preprocessing before filtering phase\n- **FilterPlugin** (line 540): Filters nodes that cannot run a pod\n- **PostFilterPlugin** (line 561): Runs when no feasible nodes are found\n- **PreScorePlugin** (line 587): Preprocessing before scoring phase\n- **ScorePlugin** (line 607): Scores nodes for the pod\n- **ReservePlugin** (line 624): Reserves resources for a pod\n- **PreBindPlugin** (line 640): Preprocessing before binding\n- **PostBindPlugin** (line 649): Postprocessing after binding\n- **PermitPlugin** (line 660): Approves or denies pod binding\n- **BindPlugin** (line 673): Binds the pod to a node\n- **Framework** (line 686): Main scheduling framework interface\n- **Handle** (line 783): Plugin context and utilities interface\n\n## Framework Runtime Implementation\n**pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/framework.go** (line 52) defines **frameworkImpl**, the component that:\n- Initializes and manages all plugins\n- Implements plugin execution methods:\n  - **RunPreFilterPlugins** (line 709): Executes pre-filter plugins\n  - **RunFilterPlugins** (line 872): Executes filter plugins for node feasibility\n  - **RunPostFilterPlugins** (line 919): Handles preemption when no nodes are feasible\n  - **RunScorePlugins** (line 1112): Scores nodes to select best candidate\n  - **RunPreBindPlugins** (line 1243): Preprocessing before binding phase\n  - **RunBindPlugins** (line 1286): Executes bind plugins to bind pod to node\n  - **RunPostBindPlugins** (line 1335): Postprocessing after binding\n  - **RunReservePluginsReserve** (line 1370): Reserves node resources\n  - **RunReservePluginsUnreserve** (line 1414): Unreserves resources if binding fails\n  - **RunPermitPlugins** (line 1454): Permits or denies pod binding\n\n## Plugin Registry\n**pkg/scheduler/framework/runtime/registry.go** defines:\n- **PluginFactory** (line 31): Function type that instantiates plugins\n- **PluginFactoryWithFts** (line 34): Plugin factory with feature gate support\n\n**pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/registry.go** contains:\n- **NewInTreeRegistry()** (line 47): Builds registry with all in-tree plugins including DynamicResources, ImageLocality, TaintToleration, NodeName, NodePorts, NodeAffinity, PodTopologySpread, NodeUnschedulable, NodeResources, VolumeBinding, VolumeRestrictions, VolumeZone, InterPodAffinity, QueueSort, DefaultBinder, DefaultPreemption, and SchedulingGates\n\n## Scheduler Orchestration\n**pkg/scheduler/scheduler.go** (line 66) defines the **Scheduler** struct which:\n- Manages the overall scheduling process\n- Contains the **Run()** method (line 464): Main event loop that calls ScheduleOne repeatedly\n\n**pkg/scheduler/schedule_one.go** (line 65) contains:\n- **ScheduleOne()** method: Orchestrates the complete scheduling workflow for a single pod, which:\n  1. Retrieves next pod from queue\n  2. Gets appropriate scheduling profile/framework\n  3. Runs PreFilter plugins\n  4. Runs Filter plugins for each node\n  5. Runs PostFilter plugins if no feasible nodes\n  6. Runs PreScore and Score plugins\n  7. Runs Bind and PostBind plugins\n\n## Architecture Flow\nThe scheduling cycle flows through: **Scheduler.Run()** → **Scheduler.ScheduleOne()** → **frameworkImpl.RunFilterPlugins()** → **frameworkImpl.RunScorePlugins()** → **frameworkImpl.RunBindPlugins()**. Each method invokes the registered plugins at their respective extension points."
}

